1. What is ReactJS?
A. ReactJS is a JavaScript library for building User Interfaces and allows developers to create simple, fast, and scalable web applications.
   ReactJS Current version - 19.1.0[ 28 March, 2025 ].
   ReactJS Previous version - 18.2.0 [ 5 December, 2024 ].
   It is maintained by Facebook.
   Its First Release was 29 May 2013.
Ex - Component-Based Architecture:
‚Ä¢  React organizes UI into reusable components, allowing developers to break down complex UIs into smaller, manageable pieces.
‚Ä¢  It is a Single Page Application. means - [ It loaded whole website in single  time & If we want to navigate to different page we can easily navigate without loading. ]
‚Ä¢  Components can be easily reused across the application, enhancing maintainability and scalability.
‚Ä¢  Header Component: Contains the logo, navigation links, and maybe user profile info.
‚Ä¢  Sidebar Component: Displays relevant shortcuts or additional navigation.
‚Ä¢  Main Content Component: Shows the main content of the page.
‚Ä¢  Footer Component: Includes copyright info, links, etc.
   Its creates Single Page Application (SPA). Becz when we open any website i.e created by ReactJS. So it download all resource, page at one time.



